io.seanbailey.model

Class Model

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.seanbailey.adapter.Model
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    User

    public abstract class Model
extends java.lang.Object
    Models can be automatically translated to and from SQL. You can also use the methods defined in this class to effectively query the database using an SQLChain.
    Since:
    2018-05-10
    See Also:
    SQLChain

      • where

        public static SQLChain where(java.lang.Class<? extends Model> clazz,
                             java.lang.String condition,
                             java.lang.Object object)
        Starts an SQLChain, that can be used to query the database for a particular set of models. Internally this makes use of prepared statements, so you don't need to worry about SQL injections.
        Parameters:
        clazz - Class to query for.
        condition - a condition that all retrieved models will meet. A question mark is used to mark the point that the object should be inserted in the prepared statement. You may also use the shorthand form "attribute", in which case "attribute = ?" will be inferred.
        object - Any Java object that can be inserted into a prepared statement.
        Returns:
        an SQLChain for further additions.
        Since:
        2018-05-14

      • find

        public static SQLChain find(java.lang.Class<? extends Model> clazz,
                            java.lang.String attribute,
                            java.lang.Object object)
        Starts an SQLChain, that lets you find a single instance of a model.
        Parameters:
        clazz - Class to query for.
        attribute - Attribute to check object against. Must be unique.
        object - Object to compare to attribute.
        Returns:
        an SQLChain for further additions.
        Since:
        2018-05-14

      • validate

        public abstract boolean validate()
        Attempts to validate the model before any database operations are carried out. Also, be sure to include an errors using addError(). Errors will be shown to the user on forms.
        Returns:
        Whether this model is considered valid.
        Since:
        2018-05-14
        See Also:
        beforeValidate(), afterValidate(), addError(String)

      • save

        public boolean save()
        Validates, and then attempts to save this model to the database. Note: you should only call this function when you wish to insert a new model into the database.
        Returns:
        Whether the model could be saved.
